data.title: Enqvist Had the Edge But…
data.meta_description: He was once ranked No. 4 in the world. He won 19 of the 26 tournament finals that he featured in. All Enqvist could manage in Grand Slams was a final loss.
data.text:
TENNIS

He was once ranked No. 4 in the world. He won 19 of the 26 tournament finals that he featured in. Besides, he helped Sweden reach the final of the Davis Cup four times in five years, winning the coveted trophy on three of those occasions.

Thomas Enqvist first came into the spotlight with an opening round upset of Andre Agassi at the 1993 US Open. While the legendary American enjoyed a long and hugely successful career, and eventually finished with a 5–5 record against the Swede, it is also a fact that in his peak years the latter led in their head-to-head meetings (4–2).

Enqvist also had better career records against the likes of Petr Korda (6-1), Michael Chang (5-1), Goran Ivanišević (5-3), Carlos Moyá (5-3), and countrymen Stefan Edberg (3-0) and Thomas Johansson (5-3). Besides, the Swede is one of the few players to have a winning record against the legendary Roger Federer (3-1).

However, all the names mentioned happen to be Grand Slam champions, while Enqvist arguably remains one of the best players to have never won any of the four trophies that matter the most. In fact, in his otherwise successful…
